## How to use on another PC

### A — slide / talk demo

Open `1_video/$event_slug_sfincs.mp4` in any media player (VLC,
Windows Media Player, QuickTime, PowerPoint, Keynote, browser).
The video shows the modelled water depth evolving with timestamp,
cumulative ERA5 rain, GloFAS Q (reference), modelled flooded area, and
max flood depth burned-in as a side panel.

### B — interactive demo

Double-click `2_interactive/$event_slug_sfincs_animation.html`. The
animation includes play / pause / reset, hourly scrubber, toggleable
overlays for EMS observed flood, EMS AOI, permanent hydrography and
cities, plus a live side stats panel.

### C — documentation

`4_docs/results.md` summarises the run + outputs. `4_docs/methodology.md`
covers the event-specific configuration on top of the shared pipeline.

## Provenance

- SFINCS v2.3.0 (Deltares, Faber et al.).
